# Backend Conventions

## File Organization
- Routes define URL paths only — no business logic. Keep handlers thin.
- Business logic goes in `src/controllers/`.
- Database queries go in `src/models/` using Drizzle ORM.
- Shared middleware (error handling, validation) goes in `src/middleware/`.

## Error Handling
- All async route handlers must be wrapped with try/catch.
- Return consistent error shapes: `{ error: string, details?: any }`.
- Use appropriate HTTP status codes — 400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 500 for unexpected.

## Database (Drizzle + PostgreSQL)
- Define schema in `src/models/schema.js`. Keep all table definitions there.
- Use Drizzle query builder — no raw SQL strings unless absolutely necessary.
- Never expose raw DB errors to the client. Log them server-side, return a generic message.

## API Shape
- Follow the conventions in `docs/03-api-design.md`.
- All responses are JSON. Successful responses return the resource or `{ success: true }`.
- No auth middleware yet — single-user MVP, skip authentication layers for now.
